verbose_text: Tripartite motif containing 9 (TRIM9), a brain specific ubiquitin (Ub) ligase, is primarily expressed in neurons and regulates netrin dependent axon guidance and morphogenesis through the interaction with vasodilator stimulated phosphoprotein (VASP), a mechanism conserved between different species.
